ZH: 我每天早上盥洗后才开始一天的工作。
EN: I start my day by washing up every morning.

ZH: 他盥洗之后，看起来焕然一新。
EN: After he washes up, he looks refreshed.

ZH: 请你在晚饭前盥洗一下。
EN: Please wash up before dinner.

ZH: 在这里盥洗可能要等一会儿，因为有很多人在等。
EN: It might take a while to wash up here because there are many people waiting.

ZH: 她收拾了一下行李箱，随后盥洗准备睡觉。
EN: She packed her suitcase and then washed up before going to bed.

ZH: 孩子们总是不喜欢盥洗的时候。
EN: Kids always dislike washing up.

ZH: 我们需要去旅馆盥洗，然后出去用餐。
EN: We need to go back to the hotel to wash up before going out for dinner.

ZH: 山里没有洗手间，我们只能在河里盥洗。
EN: There are no bathrooms in the mountains, so we can only wash up in the river.

ZH: 你盥洗得很干净，没必要再洗一遍。
EN: You washed up very clean, there's no need to wash again.

ZH: 她一边盥洗一边哼着歌。
EN: She hummed a song while washing up.

ZH: 我昨晚已经盥洗了，没必要再等半个小时在这里。
EN: I washed up last night, no need to wait another half an hour here.

ZH: 请你盥洗后再上楼。
EN: Please wash up before going upstairs.

ZH: 他洗澡的时候总是不忘盥洗。
EN: He never forgets to wash up while taking a shower.

ZH: 我已经在公共澡堂盥洗过了。
EN: I already washed up in the public bathhouse.

ZH: 他盥洗得很仔细，一点儿也不草率。
EN: He washes up very carefully, never rushing.

ZH: 请你到楼下盥洗间洗个澡。
EN: Please go downstairs to the washroom to take a shower.

ZH: 他在盥洗的时候无意中把剃须刀弄坏了。
EN: He accidentally broke the razor while washing up.

ZH: 我们只有一个盥洗间，要尽量不要同时用。
EN: We only have one washroom, try not to use it at the same time.

ZH: 在这种情况下，我得去路边盥洗一下。
EN: In this situation, I have to wash up by the roadside.

ZH: 你过来，我们一起盥洗。
EN: Come here, let's wash up together.
